The second Australian series aired on 22-24 May, 2018. It featured a Guinness World Record for the most people simultaneously observing an object in the night sky, when approximately 40,000 registered citizens watched the moon for 10 minutes on the 23rd May.

Professor Brian Cox will be joined by scientists and personalities to inspire Australia to explore our solar system. Live from Siding Spring Observatory they will tackle astronomy’s most intriguing questions. 

Following each night's Stargazing Live broadcast on ABC, Back to Earth allows viewers to journey deeper into the ideas explored on the main show and ask questions of both Brian Cox and a panel of expert scientists.


Stargazing.Live.AU.s02e01.[MPup]

Tim Minchin joins Brian Cox and Julia Zemiro on their live journey through the cosmos and Alan Duffy uses the Parkes dish to listen live for Aliens.

Stargazing.Live.AU.s02e02.[MPup]

Brian Cox and Julia Zemiro are joined by thousands of Australians to break a stargazing world record while Madga Szubanski tours the moon.

Stargazing.Live.AU.s02e03.[MPup]

Can Australia change the known age of the universe? Join Brian Cox and Julia Zemiro to find out as Stargazing Live concludes.
